\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \
\
\
\

\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \
\
\
\

\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \

\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl313\sa213\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \
\
\
\

\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \
\
\
\

\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \
\
\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \
\
\
\
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \
\
\
\
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \
\
\
\

\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \
\
\
\
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\

    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\

    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\

\'a0Enable the "GitHub Spoke" plugin. (id: com.sn.github.spoke)\
\ls201\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2.	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul \

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\

    c. Comment ID: the number above\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\

\fs28 \cf2 \ulnone Test 1: Test Delete Comment on Issues\
1. Open Flow Designer and create a new flow with Trigger "Once".\
2. Add a new Action: selection "GitHub" -> "Delete Comment on Issue".\
3. Configure the inputs:  \
    a. Owner: justforittesting\
    b. Repository: name above\
    c. Comment ID: the number above\
4. Click "Test" and verify the outputs:\
    a. Verify the outputs status is "Success".\
    b. Verify a comment is deleted in GitHub\
\

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Best Practice for Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\ul https://community.servicenow.com/community?id=community_blog&sys_id=09becbf3db589b403882fb651f961986}}

\f0\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \ulnone Webhooks :  It is way for application/app to get the real time data, anything on the server changes you get the data. Difference from traditional approach is , IN case of TA client has to keep calling the server in order to get the data, whereas in case of web hooks anythings changes on the server , application gets the data. (Works on the basis of subscribe model)\
\
Poling : Ask for the data via calling the api and get the data.\
\
\
Flow Designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
1) Flow :		 A flow consist of properties , a trigger, a sequence of actions, and the data collected or created, The trigger specifies the conditions that starts the flows when the trigger condition is true, the system starts the flow.\
2) SubFlow :  A Subflow does not have a trigger , and defines a sequence of usable actions that can be started from a flow,  subflow, or script.\
2) Action\
\
Decision Table :  It is created to resolve complex decisions and helps to reach us to the outcomes on multiple factors , In this table each factor is decision input. e.g if we are planning to buy a car we may want to make our decision based upon car driver, insurer name , place where he ,lives etc.\
\
This decision table is then further used in flow designer.\
\
Parallel Branching : Allows the user to parallel/ concurrent action. If a condition is met all parallel action will start getting executed.\
Do and until : Kind of loop type.\
\
\
\
\
London Release Flow Designer backbones :\
\
 1) Run action and flows on the MID server\
2) Power Shell\
3) Javascript on the MID\
4) REST Enhancements\
5) Integration Spokes\
\
\
\
Two components :\
A) Flow Designer\
B) Action Designer\
\
Create actions and then Flows:\
Error handling in flow designer :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
Use the Flow Execution views\
\
\
\
Header Details :\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\
